            "answer_text": "Best to look at the periodic table as see the 3 larger (19-K, 20-Ca, 21-Sc) which will lose electron to be the 18-Ar Argon structure as an cation and smaller (15-P, 16-S, 17-Cl) which will lose electron to be the 18-Ar Argon structure as an cation. Any atoms that shed or receive electrons around that 18 count will have the full Shell-3 structure of 18-Ar.  ",
